<br>
Ok here we go. I did not shout out kappaphi is a farmer. I shouted out some time later, about a few kills actually that loot is need before greed and we are not rolling for stuff to sell. Loot was announced as Need Before Greed from the start. The only reason I knew you didn't need the belt is because the cleric said in group that you sent him a tell asking if he wanted to buy it. I did not name you in the shout but we had alot of non SGA people on that raid and I wanted to make a clear point to everyone at once to make sure we were all clear on that. You handed me the belt and I gave it to a cleric that could use it. As far as I was concerned all was right with the world.<br>
<br>
I'm really sorry you took offense to that. We all took offense to the fact that need before greed is a staple loot rule and when the tell came to our cleric asking if he wanted to buy it, well we all took offense. These things happen, after my shout (which did not name you or the item) you gave it to me and I thought this was over. If this is a sticking point for you, well I don't know what to tell you.<br>
No one thinks your a loot hound. I explained to everyone how you gave it back and no one holds this against you. Then again I'm not gonna apologize for the way I handled it either. I didn't name you directly and didn't name the item.<br>
<br>
You could have just stated in /ooc ot /tell that you couldn't use it and yes we would have given your roll back.<br>
<br>
Rabbizz No it wasn't an SGA first then pickup thing, All that go on our raids get the chance to loot the only difference being a 1 hour rule that applies to late comers.<br>
<br>
